# Commit + push = release-ready changes

When the user asks to **commit and push**, treat it as a **release-ready** publish unless the user explicitly says otherwise (e.g. "do not bump version", "no release", "WIP", "draft", "no changelog").

## Required steps before committing

- Update `app/build.gradle.kts`:
  - Increment **`ncarouselLocalVersionCode`** by **+1**
  - Update **`ncarouselBaseVersionName`** when appropriate (patch/minor/major)
- Add a matching Fastlane changelog file:
  - `fastlane/metadata/android/en-US/changelogs/<versionCode>.txt`
  - Written in **English**, 2–10 short user-facing lines

## Push requirements (two remotes)

- After the commit, push to **both** remotes:
  - `git push forgejo <branch>`
  - `git push origin <branch>`

## GitHub Release expectation (automatic via CI)

- On pushes to `main`, after a green Android CI run, the workflow ensures tag `v<ncarouselBaseVersionName>` and creates/updates the matching **GitHub Release** with attached APK assets.
